cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.AR 

This paper is about Network Function Virtualization (NFV) which is a topic related to computer networks and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the analytical modeling of NFV systems, which can be related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a queuing network model, which can be related to Performance (cs.PF) and Architecture (cs.AR).
